## Phase 3: System-Level Scan

If `TOOL_LYNIS=true`, run the Lynis system audit:

```bash
sudo lynis audit system --no-colors --quick 2>&1 | tee /tmp/hipaa-lynis-$(date +%Y%m%d).txt
```

If sudo is not available, run without it (reduced coverage):

```bash
lynis audit system --no-colors --quick --pentest 2>&1 | tee /tmp/hipaa-lynis-$(date +%Y%m%d).txt
```

Map Lynis finding categories to HIPAA requirements:

| Lynis Category | HIPAA Requirement | Section |
|----------------|-------------------|---------|
| AUTH-* | Access Control | 164.312(a) |
| FILE-* | Integrity Controls | 164.312(c) |
| NETW-* | Transmission Security | 164.312(e) |
| LOGG-* | Audit Controls | 164.312(b) |
| CRYP-* | Encryption | 164.312(a)(2)(iv) |
| MALW-* | Protection from Malicious Software | 164.308(a)(5)(ii)(B) |
| FIRE-* | Transmission Security | 164.312(e) |
| KRNL-* | Integrity Controls | 164.312(c) |

If `TOOL_LYNIS=false`, provide manual check commands that the user can run:

```bash
# Check password policy
grep -E "PASS_MAX_DAYS|PASS_MIN_LEN|PASS_WARN_AGE" /etc/login.defs 2>/dev/null || echo "Not a Linux system or login.defs not found"

# Check SSH configuration
grep -E "PermitRootLogin|PasswordAuthentication|Protocol" /etc/ssh/sshd_config 2>/dev/null || echo "SSH config not found"

# Check firewall status
ufw status 2>/dev/null || iptables -L -n 2>/dev/null || pfctl -sr 2>/dev/null || echo "No firewall detected"

# Check disk encryption
fdesetup status 2>/dev/null || lsblk -o NAME,FSTYPE,MOUNTPOINT 2>/dev/null || echo "Could not check disk encryption"
```

